        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 7:32PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 732 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Stark, or near Jackson,
moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Jackson, Locust Grove, Flovilla, Mansfield, Jenkinsburg, Stewart,
Turtle Cove, Worthville, Calvin, Eudora, North Alcovy, Indian Springs
State Park, Fincherville, Stark, Rocky Plains, and McKibben.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
